<section style="padding-top: clamp(80px, 12vw, 140px); padding-bottom: clamp(80px, 12vw, 140px); padding-left: clamp(16px, 5vw, 60px); padding-right: clamp(16px, 5vw, 60px); background-color: #f5f5f5; width: 100%;">
  <div style="width: 100%;">
    {/* Top section: Two-column container */}
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 60px; margin-bottom: 50px; align-items: flex-start;">
      {/* Left column: Empty space */}
      <div />

      {/* Right column: Header + Quote */}
      <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; margin-left: auto; margin-right: 40px;">
        <h2 style="font-size: 12px; font-weight: 400; color: #888; margin: 0 0 32px 0; font-family: JetBrains Mono, monospace; letter-spacing: 0.5px; text-transform: uppercase; text-align: left;">
          /DIGITAL EXPERIENCE
        </h2>

        {/* Main Quote */}
        <p style="font-size: 22px; font-weight: 400; color: #000; margin: 0; font-family: Manrope, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5; letter-spacing: -0.01em; max-width: 600px; text-align: left;">
          EVERY ROLE HAS TAUGHT ME SOMETHING NEW<br />
          ABOUT DESIGN, PEOPLE, AND HOW GREAT WORK<br />
          HAPPENS WHEN CREATIVITY MEETS STRATEGY.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    {/* Full-width divider */}
    <div style="height: 1px; background-color: #ddd; margin-bottom: 15px;" />

    {/* Timeline entries */}
    <div style="padding-top: 5px;">
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: minmax(150px, auto) 1fr 1fr; column-gap: 40px; align-items: center; padding-bottom: 20px;">
        <div>
          <p style="font-size: 12px; font-weight: 400; color: #333; margin: 0; font-family: JetBrains Mono, monospace; letter-spacing: 0.5px; text-transform: uppercase;">
            PRESENT/1999
          </p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-left: 200px;">
          <h3 style="font-size: 22px; font-weight: 400; color: #000; margin: 0 0 10px 0; font-family: Manrope, sans-serif; line-height: 1.2;">
            SENIOR UX DESIGNER
          </h3>
          <p style="font-size: 12px; font-weight: 400; color: #888; margin: 0; font-family: JetBrains Mono, monospace; letter-spacing: 0.5px; text-transform: uppercase; text-decoration: underline; text-decoration-color: #999;">
            CHROWMDESIGNS
          </p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: 5px;">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; font-weight: 400; color: #888; margin: 0; font-family: JetBrains Mono, monospace; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0.5px; max-width: 600px; text-transform: uppercase;">
            TWENTY-FIVE YEARS IS A LONG TIME TO STAY INDEPENDENT. IT'S ALSO A LONG TIME TO BUILD A BODY OF WORK THAT MATTERS. EVERY CLIENT IS DIFFERENT, EVERY CHALLENGE UNIQUE. WHAT STAYS CONSTANT IS THE COMMITMENT TO UNDERSTANDING WHAT PEOPLE ACTUALLY NEED, THEN DESIGNING THE PATH THAT GETS THEM THERE. THAT'S WHAT CHROWMDESIGNS IS BUILT ON.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div style="height: 1px; background-color: #ddd; margin: 20px 0;" />

      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: minmax(150px, auto) 1fr 1fr; column-gap: 40px; align-items: center; padding-bottom: 20px;">
        <div>
          <p style="font-size: 12px; font-weight: 400; color: #333; margin: 0; font-family: JetBrains Mono, monospace; letter-spacing: 0.5px; text-transform: uppercase;">
            2023/2021
          </p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-left: 200px;">
          <h3 style="font-size: 22px; font-weight: 400; color: #000; margin: 0 0 10px 0; font-family: Manrope, sans-serif; line-height: 1.2;">
            ART DIRECTOR
          </h3>
          <p style="font-size: 12px; font-weight: 400; color: #888; margin: 0; font-family: JetBrains Mono, monospace; letter-spacing: 0.5px; text-transform: uppercase; text-decoration: underline; text-decoration-color: #999;">
            PENN ENTERTAINMENT
          </p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: 5px;">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; font-weight: 400; color: #888; margin: 0; font-family: JetBrains Mono, monospace; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0.5px; max-width: 600px; text-transform: uppercase;">
            PENN OPERATES ACROSS DOZENS OF PROPERTIES, WHICH MEANS BRAND CONSISTENCY IS A CONSTANT FIGHT. MY JOB WAS TO BE THE PERSON WHO CAUGHT THE DRIFT BEFORE IT BECAME A PROBLEM, WORKING ACROSS PRODUCT, MARKETING, AND EXEC STAKEHOLDERS TO KEEP THE CREATIVE ALIGNED AT SCALE. LESS ABOUT MAKING THINGS LOOK GOOD. MORE ABOUT MAKING SURE NOTHING LOOKED WRONG.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div style="height: 1px; background-color: #ddd; margin: 20px 0;" />

      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: minmax(150px, auto) 1fr 1fr; column-gap: 40px; align-items: center; padding-bottom: 20px;">
        <div>
          <p style="font-size: 12px; font-weight: 400; color: #333; margin: 0; font-family: JetBrains Mono, monospace; letter-spacing: 0.5px; text-transform: uppercase;">
            2021/2015
          </p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-left: 200px;">
          <h3 style="font-size: 22px; font-weight: 400; color: #000; margin: 0 0 10px 0; font-family: Manrope, sans-serif; line-height: 1.2;">
            SENIOR UX DESIGNER
          </h3>
          <p style="font-size: 12px; font-weight: 400; color: #888; margin: 0; font-family: JetBrains Mono, monospace; letter-spacing: 0.5px; text-transform: uppercase; text-decoration: underline; text-decoration-color: #999;">
            POCKET MADE
          </p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: 5px;">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; font-weight: 400; color: #888; margin: 0; font-family: JetBrains Mono, monospace; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0.5px; max-width: 600px; text-transform: uppercase;">
            MOST OF THE BRIEFS THAT CAME THROUGH POCKET MADE WERE HALF-FORMED. THAT WAS THE JOB: TAKE A VAGUE CLIENT ASK, RUN IT THROUGH STRUCTURED DISCOVERY, AND HAND BACK SOMETHING A DEV TEAM COULD ACTUALLY BUILD FROM. HEAVY ON USER TESTING AND JOURNEY MAPPING, LIGHT ON DECORATION.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div style="height: 1px; background-color: #ddd; margin: 20px 0;" />

      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: minmax(150px, auto) 1fr 1fr; column-gap: 40px; align-items: center; padding-bottom: 20px;">
        <div>
          <p style="font-size: 12px; font-weight: 400; color: #333; margin: 0; font-family: JetBrains Mono, monospace; letter-spacing: 0.5px; text-transform: uppercase;">
            2015/2011
          </p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-left: 200px;">
          <h3 style="font-size: 22px; font-weight: 400; color: #000; margin: 0 0 10px 0; font-family: Manrope, sans-serif; line-height: 1.2;">
            SENIOR VISUAL DESIGNER
          </h3>
          <p style="font-size: 12px; font-weight: 400; color: #888; margin: 0; font-family: JetBrains Mono, monospace; letter-spacing: 0.5px; text-transform: uppercase; text-decoration: underline; text-decoration-color: #999;">
            VOCE COMMUNICATIONS/PORTER NOVELLI
          </p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: 5px;">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; font-weight: 400; color: #888; margin: 0; font-family: JetBrains Mono, monospace; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0.5px; max-width: 600px; text-transform: uppercase;">
            AGENCY LIFE AT VOCE AND PORTER NOVELLI TAUGHT ME HOW TO WORK FAST WITHOUT GETTING SLOPPY. BRAND CAMPAIGNS, EDITORIAL SYSTEMS, DIGITAL CONTENT ACROSS TECH AND CONSUMER GOODS CLIENTS. IT IS WHERE I BUILT THE VISUAL DISCIPLINE THAT STILL SHOWS UP IN HOW CHROWMDESIGNS APPROACHES DESIGN SYSTEMS TODAY.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div style="height: 1px; background-color: #ddd; margin: 20px 0;" />
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
